  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Console Support</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">EmulatR exposes its console as a RAW TCP stream (default <text styleclass="Code Example">localhost:10023</text>) -- there is no Telnet option negotiation, so a raw-capable client is preferred. Any of the following can attach:</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox"> PuTTY (Raw)</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox"> Plink (-raw)</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox"> Tera Term (TCP/IP)</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox"> MobaXterm (TCP)</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox"> netcat (nc) -- handy for scripting and automated testing</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox"> telnet (may connect, but raw is preferred)</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">If EmulatR runs on another machine, replace <text styleclass="Code Example">localhost</text> with that host&apos;s name or IP. For development and debugging the recommended client is Plink with verbose logging:</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example">plink -v -raw localhost -P 10023</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">See TCP Console Overview for the port and auto-launch behavior, and Terminal Clients for the step-by-step connection in each program.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
